[1]                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
[2] About ten years ago, a grand AI discovery was made by three North American scientists. It is Deep Learning. It can take huge amounts of data within one single domain, and learn to predict and decide with superhuman accuracy. It can recognize one type of food from the amount of photos and create speech in various languages that the person actually had not said from many speeches the person made. These technologies have been made by America. Now, execution, product quality, speed and data are more needed and China comes in this field. Chinese people work very long hours. They work twelve hours a day for six days each week. Such a brutal environment, grows their industry including AI. More and more AI development is going on, many jobs will be replaced by AI such as Tele-sales and Reporter, and only the creative jobs will be safe. The speaker was a victim of this type of workaholic thinking. A few years ago, he was diagnosed with the four stages of forma. He realised how important it is to spend time with loved ones.                                                                                                           
[3] The speaker is Kai-Fu Lee. He talked about the rapid advancements in Artificial Intelligence (AI), particularly deep learning, and how this technology is transforming the world, largely driven by innovation in the U.S. and China. He confessed to a past mistake of prioritizing his work over his family, which, combined with a severe health issue, led him to realize the importance of love and compassion over a work-centered life. Lee argues that while AI will inevitably replace many jobs involving "simple labor" and create an "unprecedented wealth," it lacks the human qualities of love, empathy, and creativity. Therefore, the future of humanity lies in embracing "compassionate jobs," such as caregiving and teaching, and focusing on creative work. He suggests that AI can ultimately save our humanity by freeing us from routine tasks and helping us remember what truly makes us human: our capacity for love.                                                                                                                                                                                                                               
[4] Kai-Fu Lee said that humans and AI can coexist but we need to rethink human values.  He also said that it is a very important thing in our work life balance. In 1991, he became a father.However, when he became a father, he almost left his wife alone in the delivery room. He prioritized his work more than his family. He regretted these things. Yet, his work presentation is a success. His work is producing AI skills, now it is said that AI-related jobs are developing rapidly.For example, the AI deep learning skills are amazing. Deep learning is a technology that can learn human movements and other patterns by being shown large amounts of data. This technology was once led by the United States, but now China has emerged as a major player. Furthermore , China is now making rapid technological progress. In this situation, some people worry that AI might take away their job. However, he says that AI has no emotions and that only humans can work with love and compassion. Therefore, by distinguishing human work fromAI work and preserving jobs that require human compassion, he believes that our work-life balance will improve.
[5] Kai-Fu Lee talks about how AI is changing our world very fast. He explains that AI can do many tasks better than humans, such as finding patterns, working with a lot of big data, and doing the same job again and again without getting tired. Because of this, many jobs may disappear in the future. However, he also says that AI cannot feel love, care, or real understanding. It cannot show true empathy or make deep human connections. These are the things only humans can do. He believes that AI will not only take jobs but also give humans new chances. When AI does the hard and boring tasks which humans do not want to do, humans can focus on creative, caring, and emotional work. He says we will need new education systems, new job training, and fair ways to share the money created by AI. He thinks AI can help us become more human and build an efficient society.

Opinions

five sample opinions

[1] The speakers story made me think about what really matters when AI becomes more powerful. He talked about his errors in my values, like almost leaving his wife during her 12 hour labor to give an AI presentation. It shows how work can take over our lives. AI can do many tasks with superhuman accuracy, but it has no love and no real emotions. Humans can care, feel, and understand others. So when AI replaces routine jobs, I think that we should focus more on jobs of compassion and human connections. So I think that AI should help us, not replace the meaning we create.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
[2] When Im making plans, brainstorming,or need a massive amount of information, I use AI, especially Chat GPT. While appreciating the time saving and convenience that AI provides,I feel a sense of dread at the realization that we can no longer go back to time before using AI. Its a well-known fact that AI is taking human jobs, but I think that only humans can possess passion for work,and AI will likely never surpass the results that passion produces. Recently I have read manga drawn by AI, but the artwork was monotone and hard to follow, making them very difficult to read and not at all interesting. I still think that humans have an overwhelming advantage over AI when it comes to creative work. Memo Ai apple Family love 3 Hotdog Car Trump chinese 996 Weibo Wechat Facebook twitter Routine Compassion Love
[3] I agree with his ideas that AI cant replace humans in all areas of jobs,especially in creative and compassionate jobs. These days we have discussed that AI has to be taken in the trial.However I think that AI cant understand our complex minds,so it does not have to be used instead of humans. We have to judge with love and humanity.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
[4] People often say that AI will take away many jobs, and during my job-hunting process Ive been thinking a lot about which roles will remain in the future. Through this experience, I realized that there are still many things only humans can do, such as understanding emotions, building relationships, and making thoughtful decisions. This has helped me feel more confident about choosing a career where human strengths truly matter.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              
[5] I believe humans have a special kind of thinning that computers will never match. This includes our ability to make ethical choices, use our gut feelings, and understand the big picture, which goes beyond just data. AI is fantastic at giving us the best possible information and analysis. It's a perfect tool for optimization.However, the real human superpower in the future will be our ability to connect the dots. We take AIs purely logical advice and mix it with our human emotions, values, and common sense. This allows us to turn complicated data into real, meaningful action. By using AAI to get the facts, and then using our unique wisdom to decide how and why we act, we keep our essential role at the center of innovation and decision-making.
